# MANIFEST.in — ensures non-Python files ship with the package.
# P4-011 v117 ROOT FIX (Teammate 8): the previous MANIFEST.in had a
# `recursive-include rl *.csv` entry that explicitly shipped
# rl/validated_hypotheses.csv in the wheel. This was the BUG — production
# deployments inherited seed data, contradicting the audit requirement:
#   "Remove the rl/validated_hypotheses.csv file from the package. The
#    canonical path is phase1/processed_data/validated_hypotheses.csv
#    — let the writeback module create it."
#
# The canonical file is created at RUNTIME by phase4/writeback.py when
# a pharma partner validates a hypothesis. Shipping it pre-populated
# (even with real FDA historical data) created confusion about which
# entries are seed data vs runtime writeback output.
#
# ROOT FIX: the `recursive-include rl *.csv` line is REMOVED. The only
# CSV that ships in rl/ is the TEST FIXTURE at rl/tests/fixtures/
# validated_hypotheses_seed.csv (which is excluded by .dockerignore's
# `**/tests/**` rule and is not loaded by production code — only by
# tests that explicitly point to it via RL_VALIDATED_HYPOTHESES_PATH).
#
# P4-003 (the original issue) is still satisfied: the runtime CRITICAL
# log in _load_validated_hypotheses() fires if the file is missing,
# and the RL_VALIDATED_HYPOTHESES_PATH env var override works.

include README.md
include LICENSE
include requirements.txt
recursive-include rl *.py
recursive-include graph_transformer *.py
recursive-include phase1 *.py
recursive-include phase2 *.py
recursive-include tests *.py
# v113 IN-051 ROOT FIX (LOW — Corrupted): the previous MANIFEST.in
# included only *.py files from rl/graph_transformer/phase1/phase2/tests
# but did NOT include *.yaml, *.json, *.md, *.txt data files. A
# ``pip install .`` would produce a wheel missing critical data files:
#   • phase2/drugos_graph/data/label_map.yaml (KG builder crashes)
#   • phase1/data/uniprot_organism_crosswalk.yaml (entity resolution)
#   • phase1/entity_resolution/schema/v1.json
#   • phase2/data/registry.json
#   • phase2/drugos_graph/data/label_dictionary.md
#   • shared/ entirely (no recursive-include for shared/)
# ROOT FIX: add recursive-include rules for all data file types AND
# for the shared/ directory. Verified with ``python -m build`` (the
# wheel now contains all data files).
recursive-include phase1 *.yaml *.json *.md *.txt
recursive-include phase2 *.yaml *.json *.md *.txt
recursive-include graph_transformer *.yaml *.json *.md *.txt
recursive-include rl *.yaml *.json *.md *.txt
recursive-include shared *.py *.json *.yaml *.md
recursive-include common *.py *.json *.yaml *.md
